// Example of ODB class definition in C++\n  #pragma db object\n  class user {\n  public:\n      user () {}\n      user (const std::string& n): name_ (n) {}\n\n      const std::string& name () const { return name_; }\n      void name (std::string v) { name_ = v; }\n\n  private:\n      friend class odb::access;\n      #pragma db id auto\n      unsigned long id_;\n\n      std::string name_;\n  };